## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of inventory in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Inventory is the bounded tracking structure
for possession,
location,
stock,
movement,
reservation,
and depletion
of items or item-like resources.

Inventory is not the origin of item identity.
It is the governed accounting and placement layer
for tracked holdings.

## architectural_position
Inventory sits between:
- item identity
- housing/location placement
- work/quest consumption
- market/trade movement
- organization/company stock control

## required_behavior
- inventory identity/context must remain explicit
- stock/holding basis must remain explicit
- current and historical inventory states must remain distinguishable
- inbound/outbound movement must remain explicit
- reservation/depletion meaning must remain explicit

## canonical_rules
- inventory count must not redefine item truth
- reservation is not identical to consumption
- historical stock movement must remain queryable
- ambiguous inventory movement fails closed

## state_model
The inventory domain distinguishes:
- available inventory
- reserved inventory
- in-transfer inventory
- depleted inventory
- restricted inventory
- historical inventory

## actor_boundary
- inventory owner/controller
- operator
- reviewer
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if inventory context is unclear, stop movement-sensitive action
- if movement basis is unclear, fail closed
- if depletion exceeds allowed scope, deny
- if inventory becomes historical, preserve movement trace

## review_checklist
- inventory context is explicit
- stock movement is explicit
- reservation/depletion distinction is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
